{
  "text": "It has been proposed that unlike native HsRhAG, the I61R and F65S variants mediate the transport of potassium [CITATION_1] . We have previously shown that expression of HsRhAG does not allow growth of a trk1D trk2D yeast mutant defective in endogenous potassium transporters [CITATION_2] . While the F65S mutant behaved as native HsRhAG, the I61R variant conferred slow growth to trk1D trk2D cells under limiting potassium conditions (Fig. 2i ). These data suggest that HsRhAG I61R slightly alters potassium conductance in yeast.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "206873131",
